<title>INDIA: India's RBI allows dealers to borrow overseas.</title>
<headline>India's RBI allows dealers to borrow overseas.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-04-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) on Tuesday said it allowed authorised dealers to borrow up to $10 million from their overseas offices.</p>
<p>The central bank in its monetary policy for the first half of 1997/98 (April-March) said authorised dealers could also invest up $10 million in overseas money market instruments.</p>
